9. SPECTRAL TOURNAMENT POLYNOMIAL: f(A) WHERE A = ADJACENCY
======================================================================

f(A_Petersen) = A² - 5A + 6I:

  Eigenvalues of f(A): f(3)=0, f(1)=2, f(-2)=20
  So f(A) has eigenvalues 0 (mult 1), 2 (mult 5), 20 (mult 4)

  Tr(f(A)) = 0·1 + 2·5 + 20·4 = 90
  det(f(A)) = 0^1 · 2^5 · 20^4 = 0  (singular!)

  rank(f(A)) = 9
  nullity(f(A)) = 1
  The null space is the eigenspace of λ=3 (the KEY₂ eigenspace)
  = span of the all-ones vector (1,1,...,1)

